<i>Posted by Mortok on 09-13-2001 10:25 PM:</i>

<p><b> </b></p>

<p>Hiya Hopwin<br />
<br />
I was lucky enough to join Korsis when we still did epics at an alarming pace.  Its seems now that most of the people in my guild have their epics or are a few battles away.  We always rearrange our schedule to take down these mobs for epics though since for the most part they are easy fights... the warrior epic being the toughest out there and the cleric epic being the toughest camp always tests our guilds patience  <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt=""><br />
<br />
Joining CTV, Valon or even DV I would think it would be hard to pull them away from doing epics merely because their level requirements are so high that you should have your epics by then.  Korsis level requirement is 55+ so you should also by that time.  Any of the "sub Uber guilds" such as Korsis, Dawntreaders, FoF, DM and ToH and such would be good guilds to join since a lot of their members still need to do epic work and those battles for those guilds are fairly easy.   I know our guild requirements are that you are a couple battles from your epics or done.  I don't know about the other guilds though.<br />
<br />
If you plan on going with any of the other guilds out there be prepared to wait in line and also realize that some of the mobs you need might be out of the range for that guild.  Being a ranger and getting your epic in a lesser guild is still pretty easy IMHO.<FONT face="arial, helvetica" size="2"><br>
