<i>Posted by Silvarian on 09-14-2001 06:55 PM:</i>

<p><b> </b></p>

<p>Hmnns, most likely a "high end" guild won't / will not just do your epics because you don't have it. <br />
<br />
Also, all top end guilds I know usually have a "probation" period. <br />
Meaning that while you might be in the guild, don't expect them to do anything for you till you have proven that you are an asset to them.<br />
<br />
This might mean that you might have to organise you own mini raids, AND not have such raids clash with the guild's agenda. <br />
<br />
For example, a top end guild can be "raiding" every single day and you "organising" a raid that is contradictory to its agenda and thus be looked at as one for your "own ends" (especailly during your probation period) and can mean a swift kick out of the door and "blackballed" from other like guilds by word of mouth. Guildleaders do sometimes talk to other guild's leaders. <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt=""><br />
Oh Yes, probation in this case can mean anywhere from 1 month to 3 months. <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt=""><br />
<br />
Unless of course, you are well known on your server or to the guild that you are going to join either by reputation or by the members themselves.<FONT face="arial, helvetica" size="2"><br>
