<i>Posted by Locz on 09-14-2001 07:58 PM:</i>

<p><b> </b></p>

<p>Most of the "uber" (top 2 or 3 guilds) won't have the time to do your epics for you, at least until you have proved yourself to them.  For that matter, many uber guilds wouldn't even consider your application if you're a hybrid class until you are level 59+.<br />
<br />
The second-tier guilds, several of which (on Rodcet at least) are strong enough do  VS/Trak/Serv/Gor/Wuosihi/Chardok Royals/ToV are still often willing to help someone get epics.  But it might take a significant "probation" time before you will find members willing to enthusiatically help a new member get epics.<br />
<br />
Why is this?  It's my experience (in a strong second-tier guild) that far too often, a loot-greedy individual joins us just for the purpose of getting epics and ToV armor.....then as soon as their guild has helped them "become uber" they quit and apply to a first-tier guild.<br />
<br />
People who "use" their guild as a stepping stone are sleeze.  I know we are carefully trying to screen out people with this mindset.  I hope Hopwin, this is not your path.<FONT face="arial, helvetica" size="2"><br>
