<i>Posted by Liri Trueblade on 09-14-2001 09:52 PM:</i>

<p><b> </b></p>

<p>I must be lucky. In my guild, we are still working on getting epics...we can do Kael, planes, DN, a lot of places. Our sights are set on being able to do even bigger things like ToV, etc. But none of this is under any one person's rule. We work as a team, as a family. We are friends. We do screen people, but not according to their equipment. We are not an uber guild, but we have the power to do what we want, and have the friends to call in if we need/want to. We succeed because we work together. There is no agenda to cater to. We have focus, but it is the focus of the guild as a whole, not just the leader. <br />
<br />
Hopwin, I understood your concern. In my previous guild, I had not much chance at attaining epics, we just didn't have the manpower to do the bigger raids. Now, I'm in a different guild that does have that capability, but that is not why any one of us joined. We joined for the people in it. To be with friends.  I think that if someone is looking for a new guild, and wants to get their epics someday, they have a right to question the capability of the guild. Not as in "will you get me xxx" but as in if they can do it or not, or are willing to help. I would not want to just join a guild, then find out later they are not raid-capable, and have to leave, if I wanted to do certain raids or get my epics. Some folks just don't have 30 close friends on of the necessary level.  But some folks do want to go on big raids, and do big quests. There is nothing wrong with keeping that in mind, just being greedy about it is wrong. <br />
<br />
I can't tell you how many epic raids, hunts, etc., I have been on just for my guildmates, and even strangers. Personally, I enjoy seeing them get what they need. In any guild, a member should contribute to the guild, and be there to help out when they can. As well, the guild should be able to back up its members.<br />
<br />
Hopwin, good luck on your search, I hope you find a good guild, who will value you as a person, and help to challenge you as well.<FONT face="arial, helvetica" size="2"><br>
