<i>Posted by Silvarian on 09-15-2001 05:04 AM:</i>

<p><b> </b></p>

<p><blockquote><FONT face="arial,helvetica" size="1">quote:</font><hr><i>Originally posted by Cosimo </i><br />
<b>I've spent too long in guilds that just can't do anything besides the occasional succesful Kaesora group, hour long group in FM, failed Hate raid, failed VS raid, failed Faydedar raid, and a mass exodus of most 50+ that keeps them from achieving more. </b><hr></blockquote><br />
<br />
/Nods<br />
Ever wondered how your old guild would have fared had all these guild hoppers especially the 50+ ones had not left? From your description, your guild never had a chance to grow, and that is unfortunate. For a guild to grow, and to succeed, for the most part, you need people who are willing to stick it out and work as a team. Which is why "twink" guilds usually never get anywhere. The people are just using the guild as an end to a means. In this case, to level, get equipment then leave.<br />
<br />
Still a good many smaller guild have grown sucessful (that I know of) by getting people who are "builders" and not movers. You know, people who stay with the guild, and help the guild by doing stuff like organising raids, formulating tactics when they fail (and they will) and simply not giving up.<br />
<br />
Ubers and high end guilds fail alot too <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt=""> but the one thing that you will notice from high end guilds is that death (even before we had click ress) is just a slight road bump. When you have members who are willing to take xp losses / level losses just to learn how to take down mobs, who treat failure as part of the game and try again (sometimes for the 4th or 5th time) you have an "uber" guild in the making. <br />
Its just a matter of people sticking it out together and working as a team that get things done.<br />
<br />
Though sometimes, the guild itself isn't interested or just not able to do so. That's really not anyone's fault, just the way the guild was formed or is structured.<br />
<br />
Good luck though, on your new adventures with your new guild.<FONT face="arial, helvetica" size="2"><br>
