<i>Posted by Xthorn on 09-17-2001 11:14 AM:</i>

<p><b> Re: Guilds and epics</b></p>

<p>I completed my epic without a guild.  I've been guildless since level 51, it's somewhat difficult getting into any of the high level guilds, especially ones on Kael faction -- they are a bit exclusive.<br />
<br />
Most of the battles other than the PoH stone and PoA sphere do not require more than one group to complete.  So find some friends and schedule some time during which they are available to help.  You could probably interest them with incentives such as experience and loot.  Make sure you find out everything you need to know about the encounter to prevent failure.  Otherwise, your friends might get a little weary come the next time you ask for help.<br />
<br />
Choosing a guild shouldn't be a decision of whether or not they will help you with your epic, but rather if you will have more fun as part of that guild.  If their normal activities don't meet your needs, then there's no point in joining it.<FONT face="arial, helvetica" size="2"><br>
__________________<br>
Xthorn<BR>60 Warder of Karana<BR>Brell Serilis Server</font></p>
