We kill velious boss mobs and are after ST keys, but I think our smaller size allows us to concentrate on individual needs a bit better than a larger guild.  For example, I am the sole ranger in guild atm (Andilee retired), so that has it's advantages.<br />
We have our epics as well, so mostly newcomers have a need and we go outta our way to finish them, especially if the individual has shown initiative.<br />
<br />
Epics = good for any guild (unless you are banking them), and most are easy to complete (except for rarity and possible competition for spawn- *cough* Ragefire).<br />
<br />
Bottom line: choose the guild ye want and apply and do what's needed, and if ye have style, flair and substance, then ye'll get in.  Epics will soon come or something better, so I'd concentrate on passing probation/trial and put all else on backburner... if ye get in, you'll get equipped.<br />
